title.narrative: COMMUNICATIONS AND PUBLIC ADVOCACY

description.narrative: UNICEF Cambodia staff and partners are provided the guidance, tools and resources to effectively communicate, advocate and develop partnerships regarding child rights issues with stakeholders., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The Cambodia country programme is efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality results-based management standards and achieve results for children.
